## 7-Agent Pipeline Architecture

### Pipeline Definition (`_PIPELINE_AGENTS` list)

| Order | Agent ID | Name                          | Provider    | Model                               | Stage |
|-------|----------|-------------------------------|-------------|--------------------------------------|-------|
| 0     | 1        | Agent 1a: Online Data (Pplx)  | perplexity  | sonar-pro                            | 1     |
| 1     | 2        | Agent 1b: X Sentiment (Grok)  | xai         | grok-4.20-beta-latest-non-reasoning  | 1     |
| 2     | 3        | Agent 2: CSV Analyst (Claude)  | openrouter  | anthropic/claude-sonnet-4.6          | 1     |
| 3     | 4        | Agent 3: Model Reader (Gemini)| openrouter  | google/gemini-3.1-pro                | 1     |
| 4     | 5        | Agent 5: Validator (GPT-5.4)  | openrouter  | openai/gpt-5.4                       | 1     |
| 5     | 6        | Agent 4: Historical (DeepSeek)| openrouter  | deepseek/deepseek-v3.2               | 2     |
| 6     | 7        | Agent 6: Synthesizer (Opus)   | openrouter  | anthropic/claude-opus-4-6            | 3     |
| 7     | 8        | Agent 7: Auditor (Grok)       | xai         | grok-4-0709                          | 4     |

### Execution Flow (`_run_pipeline_sync`)

```
Stage 1 (PARALLEL via threading)
  ├── Agent 1a: Perplexity Sonar Pro → web search for market news
  ├── Agent 1b: xAI Grok 4.20 → X/Twitter sentiment scan
  ├── Agent 2: Claude Sonnet → CSV data analysis (theta_agg, theta_snapshot)
  ├── Agent 3: Gemini Pro → prediction.csv ML model interpretation
  └── Agent 5: GPT-5.4 → cross-validation of data
          ↓ all Stage 1 outputs collected
Stage 2 (SEQUENTIAL)
  └── Agent 4: DeepSeek V3.2 → historical pattern comparison
          ↓ receives Stage 1 outputs as context
Stage 3 (SEQUENTIAL)
  └── Agent 6: Claude Opus → master synthesis of all agents
          ↓ receives Stage 1 + 2 outputs
Stage 4 (SEQUENTIAL)
  └── Agent 7: Grok 4 → independent audit of entire pipeline
          ↓ receives Stage 1 + 2 + 3 outputs
```

Each sequential stage receives prior agent outputs via string concatenation:
```python
prior_context = "\n\n".join(
    f"--- {a['name']} ---\n{agent_outputs.get(a['id'], '[missing]')}"
    for a in _PIPELINE_AGENTS if a["stage"] <= current_stage - 1
)
```

### Pipeline is SYNCHRONOUS (Blocking)
The pipeline runs synchronously inside the Dash callback. Dash shows a loading
spinner on the outputs while the callback blocks. This is intentional — the user
wants to see all results at once when complete.

